      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEDERAL SENOR (1) took the sit on the lead from a low draw but levelled up and led around the bend to score (22.49) at The Gardens in a Grade 5 over 400m. Can measure up again. KENNY'S GIRL (2) is a safe beginner. Last start finished 4th over 400m at The Gardens beaten 10 lengths (23.19) behind FEDERAL SENOR in a Grade 5 on April 2. With even luck and a clean start should be thereabouts PONTELLA (3) has been out of the placings at her last couple but on the winners' heels when placing three back (22.41) in a Grade 5 at this track. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. SIMPLY JUAN (8) boasts a solid strike-rate over this track and distance.",
